Package com.hedera.sdk.common

Provides general classes for entities used throughout the api and to support files, transactions and smart contracts
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    HederaAccountID
    The ID for a cryptocurrency account, it is composed of a shard number, a realm number and an account number
    HederaContractID
    The ID for a smart contract, it is composed of a shard number, a realm number and a contract number
    HederaDuration
    The length of a period of time.
    HederaEntityID
    The ID for a single entity (account, claim, file, or smart contract instance) either one of accountID, claim, fileID or contractID will be set, others will be null
    HederaFeeComponents
    The different components used for fee calculation
    HederaFeeData
    The total fees charged for a trasansaction.
    HederaFeeSchedule
    The fee schedule for a specific hedera functionality and the time period this fee will be valid for the transaction
    HederaFileID
    The ID for a Hedera File which is made of a shard number, realm number and file number
    HederaKeyList
    A HederaKeyList is a list of HederaKeyPair
    HederaKeyPair
    A Key can be a public key from one of the three supported systems (ed25519, RSA-3072, ECDSA with p384).
    HederaKeySignature
    This class is a helper for managing keys and signatures in tandem.
    HederaKeySignatureList
    A HederaKeySignatureList is a list of HederaKeySignature
    HederaKeySignatureThreshold
    This class is a helper for managing keys and signatures in tandem.
    HederaKeyThreshold
    A set of public keys that are used together to form a threshold signature.
    HederaKeyUUIDDescription
    Description and UUID for a key
    HederaNodeAddress
    The information about a node
    HederaNodeAddressBook
    Gives the node addresses in the address book
    HederaRealmID
    The ID for a realm.
    HederaShardID
    Each shard has a nonnegative shard number.
    HederaSignature
    A Signature corresponding to a Key.
    HederaSignatureList
    The signatures corresponding to a KeyList of the same length
    HederaSignatureThreshold
    A signature corresponding to a ThresholdKey.
    HederaTimeStamp
    An exact date and time.
    HederaTransactionAndQueryDefaults  
    HederaTransactionFeeSchedule
    The fees for a specific transaction or query based on the fee data
    HederaTransactionID
    The ID for a transaction.
    HederaTransactionReceipt
    The consensus result for a transaction, which might not be currently known, or may succeed or fail.
    HederaTransactionRecord
    Hedera Record for a transaction
    HederaTransactionState
    This class exists in order to enable asynchronous handling of Transaction Receipts It is fully synchronised and therefore thread safe The class holds an internal hashmap of node and receipt, indexed by TransactionID Adding a transaction to the hashmap means it will be queried for a receipt when refresh() is called Transactions are automatically removed from the hashmap when the collected receipt means there is no reason to continue polling for one.
    Utilities  
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    HederaKeyPair.KeyType
    The type of key held in this object
